            {
                "box": {
                    "id": "obj-instructions",
                    "linecount": 10,
                    "maxclass": "comment",
                    "numinlets": 1,
                    "numoutlets": 0,
                    "patching_rect": [ 15.463916659355164, 515.4638886451721, 971.1340222358704, 141.0 ],
                    "text": "GETTING STARTED\n\n• In Ableton Live: open Preferences → Link, enable Audio and choose a Name. The Live track outputs are now exposed as channels named after the tracks (and the master is 'Main'). Live can also receive a remote channel by setting a track's Audio From to a peer's channel.\n\n• In TouchDesigner: use the Link Audio In CHOP to subscribe by Channel Name and the Link Audio Out CHOP to publish.\n\n• In Max (this package): use void.linkaudio.in~ to subscribe by @channel and void.linkaudio.out~ to publish under a chosen @channel.\n\n• Channel names are case-sensitive. Auto-poll handles reconnection and discovery."
                }
            }
